  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), particularly the remarkable evolution of large language models (LLMs), have given rise to a lot of services and applications that support human tasks in various domains.",
    "Generative AI with LLMs holds a strong potential for substantially changing human intellectual activities.",
    "For example, instruction-tuned LLMs (e.g., ChatGPT) can quickly generate surprisingly natural sentences in response to human questions (Wei et al., 2021).",
    "Zylowski and Wölfel (2023) revealed that when specifying personas for ChatGPT in prompts enables it to simulate a variety of personalities and capabilities.",
    "OpenAI reported that ChatGPT scored 1,300/1,600 on the SAT by eliciting knowledge in its language model."
  ],
